This paper is primarily focused on image-to-image translation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques to achieve better results, which is a common theme in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new framework for image-to-image translation, which involves the use of adversarial training and attention mechanisms, which are topics commonly discussed in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the scalability of the proposed framework, which could be relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed framework on a new animal faces dataset, which could be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
